## SS 3b. Get Post URL from Feed (clipboard approach)

🚨 **Feed posts have `postUrl: null`** — LinkedIn doesn't expose activity URNs in the feed DOM. Use the overflow menu "Copy link to post" to get the URL via clipboard. This replaces the expensive profile-hop approach (saves 4-6 steps per post).

**ONE async evaluate per post — returns postUrl and postId for grep dedup:**

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    var items = document.querySelectorAll('div[role="listitem"]');
    var item = items[${targetIdx}];
    if (!item) return { error: 'no item at idx' };
    var btns = Array.from(item.querySelectorAll('button'));
    var overflowBtn = btns.find(b => (b.getAttribute('aria-label') || '').includes('Open control'));
    if (!overflowBtn) return { error: 'no overflow button' };
    overflowBtn.click();
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 800));
    var menuItems = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('[role="menuitem"]'));
    var copyLink = menuItems.find(m => m.innerText.includes('Copy link to post'));
    if (!copyLink) {
      document.dispatchEvent(new KeyboardEvent('keydown', { key: 'Escape', bubbles: true }));
      return { error: 'no Copy link menu item' };
    }
    copyLink.click();
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500));
    var url = await navigator.clipboard.readText();
    var activityMatch = url.match(/(?:share|activity)[-%:]([0-9]+)/);
    var numId = activityMatch ? activityMatch[1] : null;
    var postId = numId ? 'urn:li:activity:' + numId : null;
    return { postUrl: url, postId: postId };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

**Usage in browse_and_engage:** For each interesting feed post (idx from SS 3), run SS 3b to get `postId`. Then batch-grep ALL postIds against tracking file BEFORE navigating to any post.

